  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he was effectively cut out of-- of many things, such as he had to acquire his hops at auctions.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at those auctions, whereas before he would have been just one of the participants, even though he still could go to them, they made sure that somebody else would outbid him and he couldn't do it.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He couldn't obtain the merchandise, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this became harder and harder.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my parents found ways of substituting some other produce where it wasn't possible with hops anymore for a while.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in season, they could ship asparagus, for which this area was renowned, to other parts of Germany and-- and to people who-- who-- who wanted asparagus from that area, and-- or grain, on a very small scale.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my-- my mother found a few items, such as special types of coffee and chocolate, that she could sell to friends and-- and relatives in town and-- and in other cities.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
